## Part B — Dedup Gap Analysis (3 Ingestion Paths)

### Path 1: Website → Stripe → PMS

| Layer | Mechanism | Status |
|-------|-----------|--------|
| `create-checkout` | `idempotency_key` check (10-min window) | ✅ Works |
| `create-checkout` | Confirmed booking overlap check | ✅ Works |
| `create-checkout` | Active hold overlap (GiST exclusion constraint) | ✅ DB-enforced |
| `stripe-webhook` | Fetches bookings by `stripe_session_id` | ⚠️ No idempotency guard against Stripe retries |
| `rpa-sync` | Dedup by `external_ref` (SELECT → UPDATE/INSERT) | ⚠️ **Race condition** — no UNIQUE constraint |

> [!CAUTION]
> **Critical Bug #1 — `rpa-sync` Race Condition**: Uses SELECT-then-INSERT (lines 76-106) for dedup. Under concurrent requests with the same `external_ref`, two requests can both see "no existing row" and both INSERT. There is **no UNIQUE constraint** on `(property_id, external_ref)` — only a partial INDEX for lookups.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Critical Bug #2 — `stripe-webhook` No Idempotency**: Stripe retries webhooks up to ~16 times. If webhook succeeds but returns non-200 due to a late error (e.g., email timeout), Stripe retries and the entire flow runs again — duplicate PMS booking + duplicate emails.

### Path 2: OTA Email → `inbound-booking`

| Layer | Mechanism | Status |
|-------|-----------|--------|
| `gmail_message_id` dedup in `email_processing_log` | ✅ Works | UNIQUE constraint on `gmail_message_id` |
| `ota_reference_id` dedup in `inbound_bookings_raw` | ✅ Works | SELECT before INSERT |
| Auto-booked bookings don't set `external_ref` | ⚠️ Secondary risk | No dedup if gmail-addon retries |

### Path 3: Public API → `public-bookings`

| Layer | Mechanism | Status |
|-------|-----------|--------|
| `booking_reference` dedup check | ✅ Works | SELECT before INSERT |
| Room overlap check + DB exclusion constraint | ✅ Works | Application + DB-level |

