## PROPOSED CHANGES (Prioritized)

### 🔴 Phase 1 — Launch Blockers (Code Changes)

---

#### 1.1 [NEW] Database Migration: UNIQUE constraint on `external_ref`

**File**: New SQL migration in `mind-meter-app-main/supabase/migrations/`

```sql
-- Prevent duplicate bookings from concurrent rpa-sync calls
CREATE UNIQUE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS uq_bookings_property_external_ref
  ON public.bookings(property_id, external_ref)
  WHERE external_ref IS NOT NULL;
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Pre-requisite**: Must verify no existing duplicates before applying. Run:
> ```sql
> SELECT external_ref, property_id, COUNT(*)
> FROM bookings WHERE external_ref IS NOT NULL
> GROUP BY external_ref, property_id HAVING COUNT(*) > 1;
> ```

---

#### 1.2 [MODIFY] `rpa-sync`: Conflict-safe INSERT pattern

**File**: [rpa-sync/index.ts](file:///e:/Hotel%20Project/mind-meter-app-main/mind-meter-app-main/supabase/functions/rpa-sync/index.ts)

Replace the SELECT-then-INSERT at lines 76-106 with:
- Try INSERT first
- If constraint violation (`23505`), fall back to UPDATE
- This eliminates the race window entirely

---

#### 1.3 [MODIFY] `stripe-webhook`: Add idempotency guard

**File**: [stripe-webhook/index.ts](file:///e:/Hotel%20Project/ask-without-cost-main/ask-without-cost-main/supabase/functions/stripe-webhook/index.ts)

At top of `checkout.session.completed` handler (after line 93), add:

```typescript
// Idempotency: if bookings already confirmed for this session, skip
const { data: alreadyConfirmed } = await supabase
  .from("bookings")
  .select("status")
  .eq("stripe_session_id", session.id)
  .eq("status", "confirmed")
  .limit(1);

if (alreadyConfirmed && alreadyConfirmed.length > 0) {
  log("Webhook already processed (idempotent skip)", { sessionId: session.id });
  return new Response(JSON.stringify({ received: true, already_processed: true }), {
    headers: { ...corsHeaders, "Content-Type": "application/json" }, status: 200,
  });
}
```

